<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1421,1568,2090]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015">
Cryptophyte, native with distribution in the Southern Cone Region of South America; previously recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[813,1055,1866,1890]" country="Argentina" name="Buenos Aires" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015">Buenos Aires province</collectingRegion>
but not from mountainous areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1421,1568,2090]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[850,1029,1899,1923]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015">Characteristics.</emphasis>
Perennial herb, 
<quantity box="[1212,1307,1899,1923]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" unit="cm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5–10 cm</quantity>
tall. Bulb solitary, globose, ca 
<quantity box="[1048,1107,1933,1957]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
in diameter. Sheaths short. Leaves to 
<quantity box="[926,994,1966,1990]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
long, parallel-veined, linear, with apex acute. Peduncles erect. Inflorescence: an umbel, with 2–10 flowers. Tepal perianth yellow, 
<quantity box="[1140,1246,2032,2056]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.5" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.5">3.5–5 mm</quantity>
long. Anthers to 
<quantity box="[813,873,2066,2090]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="1015" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long. Fruit: a capsule.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
